<subSubSection id="C328651B852EED4B7F171B9DFEBF3A1B" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8D3690852EED4C7F171B9DFC3D3A4F" blockId="3.[830,1440,1787,1903]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="B946EA82852EED4C7F171B9DFC263A33" bold="true" box="[830,947,1787,1811]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Comments</emphasis>
: the above-given records are only a couple of representative samples which were collected for study. The species is common and widespread all over 
<collectingCountry id="F3257600852EED4C795C1A5FFC363A4F" name="Bonaire, Sint Eustatius and Saba" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Sint Eustatius</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF4D66188529ED4B7CE91B46FBC33B17" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4672912" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4672912" box="[192,1110,1568,1591]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4672912/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" startId="4.[192,268,1568,1591]" targetBox="[192,1393,250,1515]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8B8D36908529ED4B7CE91B46FBC33B17" blockId="4.[192,1110,1568,1591]" box="[192,1110,1568,1591]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B946EA828529ED4B7CE91B46FEBC3B17" bold="true" box="[192,297,1568,1591]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Figure 2:</emphasis>
Adult male 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D138529ED4B7D891B44FD0F3B17" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[416,666,1570,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbudensis">
<emphasis id="B946EA828529ED4B7D891B44FD0F3B17" box="[416,666,1570,1591]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Centruroides barbudensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Sint Eustatius, dorsal and ventral views.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B8D36908529ED4B7CE91B0AFEBF3A1B" blockId="4.[192,802,1644,1851]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
The study of the 
<typeStatus id="548988328529ED4B7DAF1B0AFE713BA3" box="[390,484,1644,1667]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D138529ED4B7E261B0AFD043BA3" box="[527,657,1644,1667]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eustatius">
<emphasis id="B946EA828529ED4B7E261B0AFD043BA3" box="[527,657,1644,1667]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">C. eustatius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(temporarily housed at the Instituto de Ecología y Sistemática, 
<collectingRegion id="49F6F8728529ED4B7CE91BCCFE813BE1" box="[192,276,1706,1729]" country="Cuba" name="La Habana" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Havana</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F32576008529ED4B7D0B1BCCFEC93BE1" box="[290,348,1706,1729]" name="Cuba" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Cuba</collectingCountry>
) and the specimens recorded herein, and their direct comparison to additional samples of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D138529ED4B7F201BAEFED63BDE" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbudensis">
<emphasis id="B946EA828529ED4B7F201BAEFED63BDE" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">C. barbudensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other islands (type locality included), confirms that the synonymy proposed by Armas (1983) is correct.
</paragraph>
